Description and Requirements:
JSI Research and Training Institute, Inc. (JSI) is implementing an immunization project in South Sudan and is seeking a Communications Consultant. The Communications Consultant will be responsible for coordinating and carrying out communication activities, together with partners and Ministry of Health (MoH), to enable strengthening of routine immunization in South Sudan. The Communications Consultant will work to support the EPI to ensure the successful implementation of communication activities to improve routine immunization activities in South Sudan.arch and Training Institute, Inc. (JSI) is implementing an immunization project in South Sudan and is seeking a Communications Consultant. The Communications Consultant will be responsible for coordinating and carrying out communication activities, together with partners and Ministry of Health (MoH), to enable strengthening of routine immunization in South Sudan. The Communications Consultant will work to support the EPI to ensure the successful implementation of communication activities to improve routine immunization activities in South Sudan., Develop a workplan along with HSS Technical Consultant and JSI HQ;
Maintain partnerships with media houses;
Hold periodic journalist briefings on the immunization programme;
Organize radio talk shows for MoH and partners;
Prepare quarterly EPI bulletins for public dissemination;
Closely work with other partners supporting immunization programme including UNICEF, WHO, SS Red Cross, etc.;
Communicate regularly (e.g. via email, weekly teleconference calls, Skype) with the HQ team, including sharing documents developed;
Participating in Full Portfolio Planning (FPP) meetings and activities in order to represent JSI and secure future opportunities in South Sudan;
Other duties as assigned.

John Snow, Inc. (JSI) is preparing for the implementation of a Gavi Alliance-funded project related to COVID-19 in Mozambique and is seeking a Consultant to provide support to the Ministry of Healthâs Expanded Program on Immunization (EPI). The Consultant will work closely with JSIâs Immunization Technical Advisor to support Ministry of Health and EPI for the planning and implementation process of the COVID-19 vaccine in Mozambique. At national level, the JSI consultant would work closely with EPI Technical Working Groups (TWG) and other relevant TWGâs for COVID-19 to enable successful monitoring through active participation in the TWGâs and  development of plans and strong tools or registers for collecting vaccination data and key monitoring indicators. 
