JSI Research &amp; Training Institute, Inc. (JSI) is a public health management consulting and research organization dedicated to improving the health of individuals and communities throughout the world over the last forty years. JSI is currently seeking an outstanding Data Analyst for the Country Health Information System and Data Use (CHISU) global cooperative agreement funded by the United States Agency for International Development (USAID) in Burkina Faso. 

CHISU is a 5-year program designed to enhance host country capacity to produce high-quality health information, to optimally manage this information, and to institutionalize evidence-based decision-making. The program works with USAID- supported host country health managers, health workers, and other stakeholders to strengthen the enabling environment of health information management and strategic planning in order to: improve harmonization of fragmented information systems, reduce duplication of data collection, and improve monitoring and tracking of a countryâs own health trends and priorities.

The Data Analyst will be responsible for leading all CHISU-related data analysis and analytics activities under the direction of CHISUâs Resident Advisor for Burkina Faso. These activities include enhancing the capacity of the Government of Burkina Faso staff to enable full and sustainable utilization of the routine health information system platform managed through ENDOS, and increasing availability and interoperability of quality health data by supporting the Directorate General of Studies and Statistics and the Directorate of Information Systems in the Ministry of Health (MOH).  This is a full-time position based in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso.iption:
