The Data Analyst will assist with the following tasks:
Strengthened governance and enabling environment of host-country health information systems
Increased availability and interoperability of quality health data and information systems
Increased demand and use of health data and information to address health priorities, gaps, and challenges 
Specific responsibilities will include, but are not limited to the following:
Strengthen collection, analysis, and use of routine health data for decision  making by supporting the Ministry of Health in the data selection, collection, and processing of routine health information;
Improve capacity at the central level to collect data from multiple sources and prepare it for analysis; 
Introducing the bottleneck analysis app in the DHIS2, with support from the HMIS Specialist,  to automate data gathering and presentation within ENDOS and displaying it in a manner that facilitates systematic analysis for health programming;
Facilitate access to data that can improve its analysis leading to disaggregation by sex and other indicators, generation of insights to improve service delivery and coverage, and possibly development of a full analytics resource that can benefit all health programs
Support the DSS to advocate for data from other systems to be shared through the interoperability layer;
Support the deployment of new tools, methods and processes to enhance the production of information products (e.g. data visualizations, dashboards, GIS) and promote their uptake and use;
Provide support to the central level in data analysis methods (e.g. predictive analytics, machine learning) to improve country capacity to understand barriers to coverage, access, and quality in health programming;
Provide technical assistance to enhance capacity at the central level to use data collected through the HMIS effectively for decision-making. Plan and conduct assessments to understand barriers to information use and develop tailored interventions to improve data use;
Assist the MOH with implementing a standardised measurement of the quality of data routinely collected by programs in the national HMIS;
Promote gender equity in program implementation.

John Snow, Incorporated (JSI) is a Boston-based public health consulting firm dedicated to providing high quality technical and managerial assistance to public health programs throughout the world. JSI works extensively with national and local governments, NGOs, the private sector, and traditional leaders to expand access to services for vulnerable populations. JSI is committed to improving the health of underserved populations through innovative approaches in a range of public health areas, including HIV and TB, reproductive, maternal, neonatal and child health, nutrition, water and sanitation, technical and organizational capacity building, supply chain strengthening, strategic information management, health systems management, and policy development.

JSI is currently recruiting for a cooperating country national Monitoring and Evaluation/Strategic Information Director for a possible position with the USAID-funded Tanzania Comprehensive Client-Centered Health Program â HIV and Tuberculosis Activity (C3HP-HIV/TB). The purpose of the project will be to support the Government of Tanzaniaâs (GOT) Ministry of Health and Social Welfare, Elderly and Children (MOHCDGEC) and the Presidentâs Office- Regional Administration and Local Government (PORALG) at the central level and in target Mainland regions to deliver high-quality integrated HIV and TB prevention care and treatment services that will improve health outcomes, particularly for youth and women. C3HP-HIV/TB will increase the demand for and use of quality integrated HIV and Tuberculosis services in target regions by improving access to quality services in both facilities and the surrounding communities, promoting positive health-seeking behaviors among Tanzaniaâs populace, and enhancing the overall policy environment for HIV/TB service delivery. Should JSI be the successful bidder, this will be a full-time position based in Dar es Salaam, Tanzania. The Finance and Administration Director will oversee all project finance and administration related duties. The anticipated award date is open. The Finance and Administration Director will report to the Chief of Party.w, Incorporated (JSI) is a Boston-based public health consulting firm dedicated to providing high quality technical and managerial assistance to public health programs throughout the world. JSI works extensively with national and local governments, NGOs, the private sector, and traditional leaders to expand access to services for vulnerable populations. JSI is committed to improving the health of underserved populations through innovative approaches in a range of public health areas, including HIV and TB, reproductive, maternal, neonatal and child health, nutrition, water and sanitation, technical and organizational capacity building, supply chain strengthening, strategic information management, health systems management, and policy development.

