Responsibilities:
The HMIS Specialist will assist with the following tasks:
Strengthened governance and enabling environment of host-country health information systems
Increased availability and interoperability of quality health data and information systems
Increased demand and use of health data and information to address health priorities, gaps, and challenges 
Specific responsibilities will include, but are not limited to the following:
 Strengthen collection, analysis, and use of routine health data for decision  making by supporting the Ministry of Health in the data selection, collection, and processing of routine health information;
Improve capacity at the central level to manage health information systems and resources by supporting systems across health areas at all levels of the health system in strategic planning and governance of the National Health Information System; 
Support interoperability between the electronic logistics management information, the health management information system (ENDOS), and the community-based digitization system or other targeted systems.  This will require coordination with other donor-funded projects as well as the Directorate of Supply Chain (DGAP) and the central medical stores (CAMEG);
Support implementation of the national health information systems strategy; 
Support finalization of the information systems architecture and provide technical assistance to the ministry (DSIS and DSS) to rationalize information systems and data sources; 
Support DSS in the deployment of ENDOS at facility level in CHISU supported regions;
Provide technical assistance to enhance capacity at the central level to use data collected through the HMIS effectively for decision-making. Plan and conduct assessments to understand barriers to information use and develop tailored interventions to improve data use;
Assist the MOH with implementing the Data Quality Review module of the DHIS2 into ENDOS to ensure that there is a standardised measurement being taken of the quality of data routinely collected by programs in the national HMIS;
Guide stakeholders at the central level towards appropriate integration of parallel reporting into the national HMIS (ENDOS);
Promote gender equity in program implementation

To prepare countries for the delivery and use of COVID-19 vaccines, technical assistance and cold chain needs must be met in an urgent and efficient manner. As part of the COVAX Facility, Zimbabwe is a beneficiary of Gavi funding to provide technical assistance in preparing for the rollout of COVID-19 vaccination in 2021. 

The Immunization Technical Consultant (ITC) will be based in Harare, Zimbabwe and provide technical assistance at the national level to the Expanded Program on Immunization (EPI) and other units of the Ministry of Health and Child Care (MOHCC)/Zimbabwe government departments in the preparation and planning for COVID-19 vaccine introduction. In particular, the consultant will support the EPI and partners to identify potential COVID-19 vaccine delivery strategies leveraging both existing vaccination platforms and non-vaccination delivery approaches to best reach identified target groups.

With technical oversight from JSIâs Senior Immunization Technical Officer, the ITC will serve as the technical focal point for JSIâs Gavi COVAX TA activities and liaise with the EPI, other key technical partners (e.g. WHO, UNICEF, USAID, and others), and JSI headquarters to implement the work.re countries for the delivery and use of COVID-19 vaccines, technical assistance and cold chain needs must be met in an urgent and efficient manner. As part of the COVAX Facility, Zimbabwe is a beneficiary of Gavi funding to provide technical assistance in preparing for the rollout of COVID-19 vaccination in 2021. 

The Immunization Technical Consultant (ITC) will be based in Harare, Zimbabwe and provide technical assistance at the national level to the Expanded Program on Immunization (EPI) and other units of the Ministry of Health and Child Care (MOHCC)/Zimbabwe government departments in the preparation and planning for COVID-19 vaccine introduction. In particular, the consultant will support the EPI and partners to identify potential COVID-19 vaccine delivery strategies leveraging both existing vaccination platforms and non-vaccination delivery approaches to best reach identified target groups.

With technical oversight from JSIâs Senior Immunization Technical Officer, the ITC will serve as the technical focal point for JSIâs Gavi COVAX TA activities and liaise with the EPI, other key technical partners (e.g. WHO, UNICEF, USAID, and others), and JSI headquarters to implement the work., The Immunization Technical Consultant is expected to:
With oversight from Senior Program Manager, be responsible for the technical organization and daily management of JSIâs Gavi COVAX TA activity in Zimbabwe, in accordance with the work plan to to ensure effective implementation;
Maintain regular and close communication with EPI, UNICEF, WHO, and other relevant stakeholders at all levels; including participation in technical working group meetings at the national level
In collaboration with the MOHCC and partners, lead activities to identify potential COVID-19 vaccine delivery strategies that leverage both existing vaccination platforms and non-vaccination delivery approaches to best reach identified target groups. This includes: Development of methodology for identifying the target populations (data collection, desk reviews, etc.); Identification of other stakeholders to collaborate with; Locations where targeted people can be found; Strategies to reach them with the vaccine; Approaches for monitoring vaccine uptake;
Submit documentation and briefs on activity implementation for internal and external use and prepare presentations on activity implementation, as required, and with oversight from the Senior ITO and JSI/HQ team;
Collaborate with the JSI headquarters team in the preparation and implementation of work plan for the Gavi contract, and prepare monthly activity summaries and interim technical reports for the EPI and Gavi;
Maintain close contact (e.g. email, telephone, Skype, etc.) with the JSI headquarters team and JSI in-country office, to ensure the smooth implementation of the activity, work plans, budgets and expenditures;
Report to the JSI Senior Immunization Technical Officer in Harare;
Perform other activities, as appropriate and requested.
